   "text": "扇子自古以来就深受中国人喜爱，但现在已不只是消暑纳凉的工具，而更多地作为艺术品供人欣赏。许多扇子造型优美、做工精良，并绘有山水、花鸟、人物等精美图案，具有很高的艺术价值。中国许多著名画家和书法家喜欢在扇子上作诗绘画，展示其艺术品味。扇子常作为礼物赠予他人，表达美好的祝福和真挚的情感。如今，扇子的实用功能已大为减弱，但作为一种文化符号和艺术形式，扇子仍然在中国传统文化中扮演着重要角色。",
   "reference": "Fans have been deeply loved by Chinese people since ancient times, but now they are no longer merely tools for cooling off in summer; instead, they are increasingly appreciated as works of art. Many fans are beautifully shaped and exquisitely crafted, adorned with fine patterns of landscapes, flowers, birds, and figures, thus possessing high artistic value. Numerous renowned Chinese painters and calligraphers enjoy writing poems and painting on fans to showcase their artistic taste. Fans are often given as gifts to convey good wishes and sincere emotions. Today, the practical function of fans has greatly diminished, but as a cultural symbol and art form, they still play a significant role in traditional Chinese culture.",
