   "text": "洞庭湖位于湖南省东北部，面积很大，但湖水很浅。洞庭湖是长江的蓄洪池，湖的大校很大程度上取决于季节变化。湖北和湖南两省因其与湖的相对位置而得名，湖北意为“湖的北边”，而湖南则为 “湖的南边”。洞庭湖作为龙舟赛的发源地，在中国文化中享有盛名。据说龙舟赛始于洞庭湖东岸。为的是搜寻楚国爱国诗人屈原的遗体。龙舟赛与洞庭湖及周边的美景，每年都吸引着成千上万来自全国和世界各地的游客。",
   "reference": "Dongting Lake, located in the northeastern part of Hunan Province, covers a vast area but is quite shallow. It serves as a flood storage basin for the Yangtze River, and its size largely depends on seasonal changes. The two provinces, Hubei and Hunan, take their names from their relative positions to the lake, with Hubei meaning \"north of the lake\" and Hunan meaning \"south of the lake.\" As the birthplace of the dragon boat race, Dongting Lake enjoys a prestigious status in Chinese culture. Legend has it that the dragon boat race originated on the eastern shore of Dongting Lake as an effort to search for the remains of Qu Yuan, the patriotic poet of the State of Chu. Every year, the dragon boat race, together with the enchanting scenery of Dongting Lake and its surrounding areas, attracts tens of thousands of tourists from all corners of the country and around the world.",
