      "script": "Many people make career decisions hastily, often choosing a job without fully thinking it through. They may become bored after a short time or spend a long period searching for their next role. To avoid this, you should carefully evaluate each opportunity. Start by seeing if there are chances for promotion. Beyond that, consider factors like the qualifications you have, the pay offered, the culture of your target company, and the overall work environment. \n\nNow let’s turn to a different kind of choice: cultural celebration. For African-Americans, Kwanzaa is as important as Christmas. It is a cultural festival founded to remind them of their heritage and struggles, and to urge them to do more for their community. One of its core principles is faith in self-determination, and the name itself refers to the first fruits of the harvest. During the celebration, families often recite one of the seven principles, such as unity or cooperative economics.\n\nFinally, think about dietary choices. The Mediterranean diet is widely considered one of the world’s most healthy diets. A landmark study on this diet, conducted across seven countries in the 1950s, is regarded as one of the greatest researches of its kind. It involved over 13,000 participants from Asia, Europe, and America, and its findings continue to influence nutrition science today.",
